"{\"uid\": \"ncregister.com-cna-vatican-deplores-olympic-offense-done-to-many-christians\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"EWTN News, Inc. is the world's largest Catholic news organization, comprised of television, radio,                 print and digital media outlets, dedicated to reporting the truth in light of the Gospel and the                 Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 4, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EWTN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"EWTN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EWTN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EWTN\"}, {\"begin\": 39, \"end\": 47, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999994629434, \"rank\": 5.367992105332909e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"score\": 0.9990471145538157, \"rank\": 0.0008893852389502828, \"text\": \"Gospel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\"}, {\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.910992372554764e-14, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe for just$49.95$32.50!\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversial scene, part of the 1.5-billion-euro (about $1.62 billion) spectacle to kick off the 2024 Summer Olympics, featured drag queens portraying the apostles.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the July 26 Paris Olympics opening ceremony that mocked the Last Supper - and after theFrench bishopsandother Catholicandworld leadersdecried the display - the Vatican on Saturday issued a statement denouncing the scene.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a brief statement emailed to journalists in French, the Holy See said it \\\"was saddened by certain scenes at the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic Games and cannot but join the voices raised in recent days to deplore the offense done to many Christians and believers of other religions.\\\"\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 746, \"end\": 754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"score\": 0.9999999989108801, \"rank\": 1.0887942070987863e-09, \"text\": \"Holy See\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Holy_See\"}, {\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9997070451301313, \"rank\": 0.00015819710844196066, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In a prestigious event where the whole world comes together around common values, there should not be allusions ridiculing the religious convictions of many people,\\\" the statement continued.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversial scene, part of the 1.5-billion-euro (about $1.62 billion) spectacle to kick off the 2024 Summer Olympics, featured drag queens portraying the apostles and a self-proclaimed lesbian DJ as Jesus in what appeared to be part of a fashion show - apparently mocking Leonardo da Vinci's famous painting.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1380, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999295891964, \"rank\": 7.04109021104168e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.877685146707378e-24, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Freedom of expression, which is obviously not called into question, finds its limit in respect for others,\\\" the Holy See concluded in its statement.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Saturday's statement comes in the wake of anopen letter issued by Catholic cardinals and bishopsfrom around the world on Friday calling on the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to \\\"repudiate\\\" and \\\"apologize\\\" for the \\\"intentionally hateful mockery\\\" of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1708, \"end\": 1716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999994629434, \"rank\": 5.367992105332909e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1785, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the letter - signed by three cardinals and 24 bishops - the prelates stated: \\\"It is hard to understand how the faith of over 2 billion people can be so casually and intentionally blasphemed.\\\"\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The signatories, led by Cardinal Raymond Leo Burke; Cardinal Wilfrid Fox Napier, OFM; and Cardinal Berhaneyesus Demerew Souraphiel, CM, also called for \\\"a day of prayer and fasting in reparation for this blasphemy.\\\"\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2144, \"end\": 2161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Leo_Burke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Raymond Leo Burke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Leo_Burke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Leo_Burke\"}, {\"begin\": 2152, \"end\": 2161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Burke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.899277575388888e-14, \"text\": \"Leo Burke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Burke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Burke\"}, {\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franciscans\", \"score\": 0.9999994155588754, \"rank\": 5.824456552825628e-07, \"text\": \"OFM\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franciscans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franciscans\"}, {\"begin\": 2210, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berhaneyesus_Demerew_Souraphiel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berhaneyesus Demerew Souraphiel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berhaneyesus_Demerew_Souraphiel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berhaneyesus_Demerew_Souraphiel\"}, {\"begin\": 2243, \"end\": 2245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Congregation_of_the_Mission\", \"score\": 0.9999999974534148, \"rank\": 2.54644843821025e-09, \"text\": \"CM\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Congregation_of_the_Mission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Congregation_of_the_Mission\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The committee said it had updated its policies to ensure 'fair and safe competition environments for women.'\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbian judo world champion Nemanja Majdov was hit with a five-month ban by the International Judo Foundation (IJF) after having made the ancient Christian sign while competing in the Paris games in July.\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2438, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbian_Orthodox_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999981167938583, \"rank\": 1.1120667980455223e-06, \"text\": \"Serbian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbian_Orthodox_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbian_Orthodox_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 2466, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nemanja_Majdov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nemanja Majdov\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nemanja_Majdov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nemanja_Majdov\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.054257690077477e-14, \"text\": \"Judo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judo\"}, {\"begin\": 2584, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999890757509164, \"rank\": 1.0924368318566485e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999176907, \"rank\": 8.214633294702626e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"COMMENTARY: The Imane Khelif case undermines the case for 'queer' as a protection for the weak.\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hocker is the first U.S. athlete to win first place in the men's 1,500-meters' race since 2016 - and his Catholic high school could not be prouder.\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999994629434, \"rank\": 5.367992105332909e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas More Society attorney Michael McHale said the plaintiffs in the case 'felt forced to succumb to a manifestly irrational mandate' without any exemption for their sincere religious beliefs.\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 3084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2890, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_More\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5212307546543493e-32, \"text\": \"Thomas More\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_More\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_More\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bishop Neary praised CRS for embodying the Church's mission of compassionate accompaniment of those in need.\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3086, \"end\": 3092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9935124633971355, \"rank\": 0.006529899564600939, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 3107, \"end\": 3110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Relief_Services\", \"score\": 0